<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id78032724-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460ppp–1"><num value="460ppp–1">§ 460ppp–1.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">As used in this subchapter:</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id78032725-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460ppp–1/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> The term “Secretary” means the Secretary of the Interior.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id78032726-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460ppp–1/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> The term “public lands” has the meaning stated in <ref href="/us/usc/t43/s1702/e">section 1702(e) of title 43</ref>.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id78032727-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460ppp–1/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> The term “conservation area” means the Black Rock Desert-High Rock Canyon Emigrant Trails National Conservation Area established pursuant to <ref href="/us/usc/t16/s460ppp–2">section 460ppp–2 of this title</ref>.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id78032728-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/106/554/s1/a/4/dB/tI/s125">Pub. L. 106–554, § 1(a)(4) [div. B, title I, § 125 [§ 3]</ref>], <date date="2000-12-21">Dec. 21, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/2763">114 Stat. 2763</ref>, 2763A–229, 2763A–354.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
